x4freetext: -COMPLETE SPECTROSCOPY OF Y-90 VIA THE Y-89(N,G) AND
Y-89(D,P) REACTIONS.
THE ILL HIGH-FLUX REACTOR.
.THERMAL NEUTRONS. THE SAMPLE WAS IRRADIATED IN THE H7
IN-PILE POSITION WITH A NEUTRON FLUX OF
5.E+14 NEUTRONS/CM2/SEC.
.THE TARGET CONSISTED OF APPROXIMATELY 290 MG OF PURI-
FIED Y2O3 POWDER, CONTAINED IN A CYLINDER OF REACTOR-
GRADE GRAPHITE. FOR ENERGY AND EFFICIENCY CALIBRATION
WITH RESPECT TO THE CL-36 STANDARD, 15 MG OG NACL WAS
ADDED TO THE YTTRIUM-OXIDE TARGET IN A SECOND RUN.
THE GAMMA-RAYS WERE DETECTED WITH A CENTRAL
GE DETECTOR, SURROUNDED BY TWO NAI DETECTORS.
THE SPECTROMETER WAS OPERATED SIMULTANEOUSLY IN TWO
DIFFERENT MODES. FOR ENERGIES UP TO 3.5 MEV THE COMP-
TON SUPPRESSED MODE WAS USED AND FOR ENERGIES ABOVE
2 MEV THE SYSTEM WAS RUN AS A PAIR SPECTROMETER. THE
ENERGY RESOLUTION WAS 1.9 KEV FWHM AT 2 MEV AND 4.6
KEV AT 7 MEV.
THE CL-36 TRANSITIONS WERE
USED AS A STANDARD FOR BOTH ENERGY AND INTENSITY.
.THE GAMMA-RAY ENERGIES WERE NOT CORRECTED FOR RECOIL.
THE SYSTEMATIC ERRORS ARE 10 PPM BELOW 3 MEV
AND 15 PPM ABOVE 3 MEV.
